<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em>Title of webpage</em>. (Year of publication). Website Name. URL
</blockquote>
<br>
If content is likely to change over time, include a retrieval date before the URL. When a 
publication date is not available, use n.d. for &#8216;no date&#8217;.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em>Title of webpage</em>. (n.d.). Website Name. Retrieved Month Day, Year, from URL
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of webpage">Swim with whales: An unforgettable wildlife encounter</span></em>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2018</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Website Name">Ocean Swim Adventures</span>. 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="URL">http://en.whales.org/encounters/big_whales</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
The URL is displayed as a hyperlink.
